ce:section.ce:para:
For understanding materials surface chemistry, the GO, CD and carbon fiber samples were examined by XPS and Raman, as shown in Fig. 5
                     . Fig. 5a reveals the XPS survey spectra of the CF, CD, GO, rGO/CF and rGO+CD/CF samples, which provide detailed information of their elemental composition (Table 1
                     ). From the O1s and C1s peaks, it can be calculated that the CF sample had the highest carbon/oxygen (C/O) ratio of 34.3. Due to the existence of a large amount of oxygen-containing groups, both GO and CD samples had a low C/O ratio (1.8 and 2.3, respectively). Electrochemical deposition reduces graphene oxide to graphene and increases the C/O ratio, therefore the rGO/CF and rGO+CD/CF samples had the ratio of 17 and 15.2 respectively, the existence of CD had little effect on GO reduction.
